//! # A2A-RS Integration Code
//!
//! This module contains the A2A (Agent-to-Agent) protocol integration code generated
//! from the RDF ontology by ggen. It provides type-safe interfaces for agent communication,
//! task management, and message handling.
//!
//! ## Overview
//!
//! The A2A protocol enables secure, reliable communication between autonomous agents
//! with support for:
//!
//! - **Agent Identity & Discovery**: Agents can announce their capabilities and discover peers
//! - **Message Routing**: Flexible message routing with QoS guarantees
//! - **Task Execution**: Distributed task execution with state tracking
//! - **Security**: Authentication, authorization, and encryption support
//!
//! ## Modules
//!
{% for module in modules | default(value=["agent", "message", "task", "transport", "skill", "error"]) %}
//! - [`{{ module }}`]: {{ module | capitalize }}-related functionality
{% endfor %}
//!
//! ## Quick Start
//!
//! ```rust,no_run
//! use {{ crate_name | default(value="a2a") }}::prelude::*;
//!
//! #[tokio::main]
//! async fn main() -> Result<(), Box<dyn std::error::Error>> {
//!     // Create an agent
//!     let agent = UnifiedAgent::builder()
//!         .id("agent-001")
//!         .name("My Agent")
//!         .build()?;
//!
//!     // Create a message
//!     let message = ConvergedMessage::builder()
//!         .source("agent-001")
//!         .target("agent-002")
//!         .payload(UnifiedContent::text("Hello, Agent!"))
//!         .build()?;
//!
//!     Ok(())
//! }
//! ```
//!
//! ## Prelude
//!
//! The [`prelude`] module re-exports common types for convenience:
//!
//! ```rust,no_run
//! use {{ crate_name | default(value="a2a") }}::prelude::*;
//! ```

